The paper deals with cost-sensitive classification using AdaBoost, which is a popular machine learning algorithm. The paper presents an empirical study of various approaches to cost-sensitive AdaBoost and evaluates their performance on a range of classification problems. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given the focus on machine learning and classification, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV.
